[32m"Masked text for sample 13, segment 2874-3678: .\n\nLet me try again.\n\nTo solve the problem, let's first translate the given conditions into mathematical equations. We are given that:\n\n1. When the students are divided into groups of 8, the last group has 5 students. This can be written as:\n\\[ N \\equiv 5 \\pmod{8} \\]\n2. When the students are divided into groups of 6, the last group has 3 students. This can be written as:\n\\[ N \\equiv 3 \\pmod{6} \\]\n\nWe need to find all possible values of \\(N\\) that satisfy both congruences and are less than 50. Let's start by finding the general form of \\(N\\) that satisfies the first condition \\(N \\equiv 5 \\pmod{8}\\). This means:\n\\[ N = 8k + 5 \\]\nfor some integer \\(k\\).\n\nNext, we need to find which of these values also satisfy the second condition \\(N \\equiv 3 \\pmod{6}\\). Substituting \\(N = 8k + 5\\) into the second condition, we get:\n\\[ 8k + 5 \\equiv 3 \\pmod{6} \\]\nSimplifying, we get:\n\\[ 8k \\equiv -2 \\pmod{6} \\]\nSince \\(8 \\equiv 2 \\pmod{6}\\), we can simplify further:\n\\[ 2k \\equiv -2 \\pmod{6} \\]\n\\[ 2k \\equiv 4 \\pmod{6} \\]\n\\[ k \\equiv 2 \\pmod{3} \\]\nThis means:\n\\[ k = 3m + 2 \\]\nfor some integer \\(m\\). Substituting this back into the expression for \\(N\\), we get:\n\\[ N = 8(3m + 2) + 5 = 24m + 16 + 5 = 24m + 21 \\]\nSo, \\(N\\) can be written as:\n\\[ N = 24m + 21 \\]\nWe need to find all values of \\(N\\) that are less than 50. This gives us:\n\\[ 24m + 21 < 50 \\]\n\\[ 24m < 29 \\]\n\\[ m < \\frac{29}{24} \\approx 1.21 \\]\nSince \\(m\\) is an integer, \\(m\\) can be 0 or 1. So, the possible values of \\(N\\) are:\n\\[ N = 24 \\cdot 0 + 21 = 21 \\]\n\\[ N = 24 \\cdot 1 + 21 = 45 \\]\nThe sum of all possible values of \\(N\\) is:\n\\[ 21 + 45 = 66 \\]\n\nLet's verify this using Python code to ensure accuracy.\n```python\n# We need to find all values of N that satisfy the conditions\npossible_values = []\n\n# Iterate over possible values of m\nfor m in range(2):  # m can be 0 or 1\n    N = 24 * m + 21\n    if N < 50:\n        possible_values.append(N)\n\n# Sum of all possible values of N\nsum_possible_values = sum(possible_values)\nprint((possible_values, sum_possible_values))\n```\n```output\n([21, 45], 66)\n```\nThe possible values of \\(N\\) that satisfy the conditions are 21 and 45. The sum of these values is \\(21 + 45 = 66\\).\n\nThus, the sum of all possible values of \\(N\\) is \\(\\boxed{66}\\).\n\nWait, let me recheck my solution.\n\n"[0m
