[32m"Masked text for sample 15, segment 4955-5715: .\n\nLet me try again.\n\nDr. Hugo Grumpus and his assistant, Igor, were preparing to perform a laboratory experiment.  Dr. Grumpus told Igor to gather 16 test tubes, 7 beakers, and 14 Petri dishes, and to place them all on the lab bench.  By accident, Igor gathered half as many test tubes as requested, two more than the number of Petri dishes requested, and he lost several beakers on the way to the lab bench.  In total, the number of items Igor had placed on the lab bench was 29.  How many beakers did Igor lose?\n$\\textbf{(A) }1\\qquad\\textbf{(B) }2\\qquad\\textbf{(C) }3\\qquad\\textbf{(D) }4\\qquad \\textbf{(E) }5$\nLet's solve the problem step by step using reasoning and Python code.\n\n1. Determine the number of test tubes Igor gathered.\n2. Determine the number of Petri dishes Igor gathered.\n3. Determine the number of beakers Igor gathered.\n4. Calculate the total number of items Igor placed on the lab bench.\n5. Determine how many beakers Igor lost by subtracting the total number of items Igor placed on the lab bench from the total number of items requested.\n\nHere are the steps in detail:\n\n1. The number of test tubes requested is 16. Since Igor gathered half as many test tubes as requested, he gathered \\( \\frac{16}{2} = 8 \\) test tubes.\n2. The number of Petri dishes requested is 14. Since Igor gathered two more than the number of Petri dishes requested, he gathered \\( 14 + 2 = 16 \\) Petri dishes.\n3. Let the number of beakers Igor gathered be \\( b \\).\n4. The total number of items Igor placed on the lab bench is 29. This includes 8 test tubes, 16 Petri dishes, and \\( b \\) beakers. So we have the equation:\n\\[ 8 + 16 + b = 29 \\]\n5. Solving for \\( b \\):\n\\[ 24 + b = 29 \\]\n\\[ b = 29 - 24 \\]\n\\[ b = 5 \\]\n\nSince Igor gathered 7 beakers but only placed \\( b = 5 \\) beakers on the lab bench, he lost \\( 7 - 5 = 2 \\) beakers.\n\nLet's verify this with Python code.\n```python\n# Given values\ntest_tubes_requested = 16\nbeakers_requested = 7\npetri_dishes_requested = 14\ntotal_items_placed = 29\n\n# Igor's gathered items\ntest_tubes_gathered = test_tubes_requested // 2\npetri_dishes_gathered = petri_dishes_requested + 2\nbeakers_gathered = beakers_requested  # Initially, we assume he gathered the correct number\n\n# Total items Igor placed on the lab bench\ntotal_items_placed_by_igor = test_tubes_gathered + petri_dishes_gathered + beakers_gathered\n\n# Calculate the number of beakers lost\nbeakers_lost = beakers_gathered - (total_items_placed - (test_tubes_gathered + petri_dishes_gathered))\n\nprint(beakers_lost)\n```\n```output\n2\n```\nThe number of beakers Igor lost is \\(\\boxed{2}\\).\n\nWait, let me recheck my solution.\n\n"[0m
